\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 5. A. lavateriflora} (DC.) Boiss.,{\i  op. cit.} 828 (1867) ({\i Althaea pontica} sensu Hayek pro parte, non (Janka) Baker fil.). Stem tomentose or glabrescent, usually setose with long, deflexed hairs. Lower leaves palmatifid, the upper palmatisect, all tomentose with yellowish, stellate hairs, and with prominent veins beneath. Epicalyx-segments narrowly triangular, acute, 2/3-4/5 as long as the sepals. Petals c. 35 × 35 mm, violet with yellow base. Mericarps with a rather shallow furrow on dorsal face; angles shortly winged.{\i  Turkey-in-Europe} ({\i Bosphorus region}). Tu. ({\i S.W. Asia}.)
