\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 6. A. rugosa} Alef., {\i Österr. Bot. Zeitschr.}{\b  12}: 254 (1862) (incl. {\i A. taurica} Iljin, {\i A. novopokrovskyi} Iljin). Stem with persistent tomentum and also villous with longer white hairs. Leaves 5-lobed, the upper more deeply (up to 2/3 of the radius), with oblong, obtuse, irregularly crenate lobes, densely tomentose on both surfaces when young, later variably glabrescent; veins very prominent beneath. Epicalyx-segments deltate, as broad as the sepals but only half as long. Petals 35 × 55 mm, pale or clear yellow. Mericarps 5-6 mm, pale brown; dorsal face usually deeply furrowed; angles produced into divergent wings; lateral faces appressed-setose.{\i  Ukraine and S. Russia.} Rs (W, K, E).
